{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"050c1de2-c7ee-43e7-8fb7-882321aabbea","content":"No files found in the workspace — I'll answer directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` element pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Key change:** the single line `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` is all that's needed. The XAML compiler resolves every `{Binding ...}` against that type at compile time.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** (not warnings) for typos or missing properties — e.g., `{Binding Themee}` will fail the build.\n\nTo make sure this isn't silently disabled, confirm two things in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- These should NOT be present (they disable compiled bindings) -->\n<!-- <MauiEnableXamlCBindingWithSourceCompilation>false</MauiEnableXamlCBindingWithSourceCompilation> -->\n```\n\nAnd **avoid `x:DataType=\"\"` (empty string)** anywhere in the tree — that opts out of compile-time checking for that subtree.\n\n## Quick Rules\n\n| Pattern | Compile-time checked? |\n|---|---|\n| `x:DataType=\"vm:Foo\"` + `{Binding Prop}` | ✅ Yes |\n| No `x:DataType` + `{Binding Prop}` | ❌ No (reflection at runtime) |\n| `x:DataType=\"\"` to opt out locally | ❌ No (intentional escape hatch) |\n\nUse the empty-string escape hatch only when binding to something outside your ViewModel (e.g., `{Binding Source={x:Reference slider}, Path=Value}`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"560365fd-35e4-4760-a949-b0123d4ec9e6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking a conceptual question about converting a .NET MAUI page to use compiled bindings. They don't have actual files - they're describing a scenario and want guidance. Let me provide the answer directly.","outputTokens":778,"requestId":"9BDC:237CD0:615F383:6C8DDAE:69EC0DF2"},"id":"53f59f19-e672-4068-9f66-ac4d7a3ede96","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:41.864Z","parentId":"6d9cac86-46a8-41a0-9c36-7ec920ea8234"}
